    CRUD
    |
    |----client
    |----server {terminal - npm init -y}

    > npm init vite
    > enter project name
    > select frame work react
    - go to client directory 
    > npm install : it will install all packages
    > npm run dev : to run the server
    > npm install bootstrap axios react-router-dom(
        bootstrap - for designing
        axios - request support*
        react-router - for routing
    )


    ==== In server ====
        1st enter into the server folder
   1) to add json file inti server folder write command:
        > npm init -y

    2)
        > npm install express mongoose cors nodemon
            -install express (framework of node.js) we will create rest api through this
            -install mongoose used for mongo database
            -install cors to access backend side into front end side
            - nodemon automatically refresh server side whenever we made changes and  update it automatically.

        3) create index.js 
        4) go to the package.json and inside it script write :
            "start": "nodemon index.js"


====================To create connection with mongo db ================
there are 2 ways i.e online and offline to connect here use offline mode

        install mongodb compas
        create database : crud
        now create on collection in it i.e:- user

        with the help of mongoose.connect() make connection with mongo db .pass connection string to this method(You will get this string by clicking on 3 dots of your database connection in mongo compas).


